      "*": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b><a href=\"/Main_Page\" title=\"Main Page\">Home</a> * <a href=\"/People\" title=\"People\">People</a> * Joe Culberson</b>\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:162px;\"><a href=\"http://webdocs.cs.ualberta.ca/%7Echinook/authors/\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/1/15/Joeculberson.jpg\" width=\"160\" height=\"220\" class=\"thumbimage\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/File:Joeculberson.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Joe Culberson <sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></div></div></div> \n<p><b>Joseph C. (Joe) Culberson</b>,<br />\na Canadian computer scientist, and professor at the Department of Computing Science, <a href=\"/University_of_Alberta\" title=\"University of Alberta\">University of Alberta</a>. \nHis research interests tends to be a mixture of theoretical analysis and experimental simulation of <a href=\"/Algorithms\" title=\"Algorithms\">algorithms</a> and <a href=\"/Data\" title=\"Data\">data structures</a>. \nIt includes <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Binary_search_tree\">binary search trees</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Graph_coloring\">graph coloring</a>, <a href=\"/Genetic_Programming\" title=\"Genetic Programming\">genetic algorithms</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>, and research on various <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Combinatorial_game_theory\">combinatorical</a> and <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Abstract_strategy_game\">abstract strategy games</a>, \nsuch as <a href=\"/index.php?title=Sokoban&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Sokoban (page does not exist)\">Sokoban</a> and <a href=\"/Checkers\" title=\"Checkers\">Checkers</a>. In winter 1988, Joe Culberson and <a href=\"/Duane_Szafron\" title=\"Duane Szafron\">Duane Szafron</a> asked <a href=\"/Jonathan_Schaeffer\" title=\"Jonathan Schaeffer\">Jonathan Schaeffer</a> \nthe innocent question \"Jonathan, what ever happened to computer checkers?\" <sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>, yielding in the development of <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chinook_%28draughts_player%29\">Chinook</a>, and solving Checkers <sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>. \nHe developed the first version of the Chinook <a href=\"/Endgame_Tablebases\" title=\"Endgame Tablebases\">endgame database</a> code <sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> . \n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Selected_Publications\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Selected Publications</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#1984_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">1984 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#1990_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">1990 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#2000_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2000 ...</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#External_Links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External Links</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Selected_Publications\">Selected Publications</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Joe_Culberson&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Selected Publications\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<p><sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> <sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"1984_...\">1984 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Joe_Culberson&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: 1984 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Joe Culberson</a> (<b>1984</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://webdocs.cs.ualberta.ca/~joe/Abstracts/msc.html\">Updating Binary Trees</a></i>.  M.Sc. thesis, <a href=\"/University_of_Waterloo\" title=\"University of Waterloo\">University of Waterloo</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Joe Culberson</a> (<b>1985</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://dl.acm.org/doi/10.1145/22145.22168\">The Effect of Updates in Binary Search Trees</a></i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://dblp.uni-trier.de/db/conf/stoc/stoc85.html\">STOC 1985</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Joe Culberson</a> (<b>1986</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://webdocs.cs.ualberta.ca/~joe/Abstracts/phd.html\">The Effect of Asymmetric Deletions on Binary Research Trees</a></i>. Ph.D. thesis, <a href=\"/University_of_Waterloo\" title=\"University of Waterloo\">University of Waterloo</a>, advisor <a href=\"/Mathematician#JIMunro\" title=\"Mathematician\">J. Ian Munro</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Mathematician#RBaezaYates\" title=\"Mathematician\">Ricardo Baeza-Yates</a>, <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Joe Culberson</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://mitpress.mit.edu/contributors/gregory-j-e-rawlins\">Gregory J. E. Rawlins</a> (<b>1988</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://link.springer.com/chapter/10.1007/3-540-19487-8_20\">Searching with Uncertainty (Extended Abstract)</a></i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://dblp.uni-trier.de/db/conf/swat/swat88.html\">SWAT 1988</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Joe Culberson</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://dblp.uni-trier.de/pers/r/Rudnicki:Piotr.html\">Piotr Rudnicki</a> (<b>1989</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://kundoc.com/pdf-a-fast-algorithm-for-constructing-trees-from-distance-matrices-.html\">A Fast Algorithm for Constructing Trees from Distance Matrices</a></i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Information_Processing_Letters\">Information Processing Letters</a>, Vol. 30</li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Joe Culberson</a>, <a href=\"/Mathematician#JIMunro\" title=\"Mathematician\">J. Ian Munro</a> (<b>1989</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.researchgate.net/publication/220458215_Explaining_the_Behaviour_of_Binary_Search_Trees_Under_Prolonged_Updates_A_Model_and_Simulations\">Explaining the Behaviour of Binary Search Trees Under Prolonged Updates: A Model and Simulations</a></i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Computer_Journal\">The Computer Journal</a>, Vol. 32, No. 1</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"1990_...\">1990 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Joe_Culberson&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: 1990 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Joe Culberson</a>, <a href=\"/Mathematician#JIMunro\" title=\"Mathematician\">J. Ian Munro</a> (<b>1990</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/BF01840390\">Analysis of the Standard Deletion Algorithms in Exact Fit Domain Binary Search Trees</a></i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Algorithmica\">Algorithmica</a>, Vol. 5, No. 3</li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Jonathan_Schaeffer\" title=\"Jonathan Schaeffer\">Jonathan Schaeffer</a>, <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Joe Culberson</a>, <a href=\"/index.php?title=Norman_Treloar&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Norman Treloar (page does not exist)\">Norman Treloar</a>, <a href=\"/index.php?title=Brent_Knight&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Brent Knight (page does not exist)\">Brent Knight</a>, <a href=\"/Paul_Lu\" title=\"Paul Lu\">Paul Lu</a>, <a href=\"/Duane_Szafron\" title=\"Duane Szafron\">Duane Szafron</a> (<b>1991</b>). <i>Checkers Program to Challenge for World Championship</i>. SIGART Bulletin, Vol. 2, No. 2</li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Jonathan_Schaeffer\" title=\"Jonathan Schaeffer\">Jonathan Schaeffer</a>, <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Joe Culberson</a>, <a href=\"/index.php?title=Norman_Treloar&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Norman Treloar (page does not exist)\">Norman Treloar</a>, <a href=\"/index.php?title=Brent_Knight&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Brent Knight (page does not exist)\">Brent Knight</a>, <a href=\"/Paul_Lu\" title=\"Paul Lu\">Paul Lu</a>, <a href=\"/Duane_Szafron\" title=\"Duane Szafron\">Duane Szafron</a> (<b>1991</b>). <i>Reviving the Game of Checkers</i>. <a href=\"/2nd_Computer_Olympiad#Workshop\" title=\"2nd Computer Olympiad\">Heuristic Programming in AI 2</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Jonathan_Schaeffer\" title=\"Jonathan Schaeffer\">Jonathan Schaeffer</a>, <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Joe Culberson</a>, <a href=\"/index.php?title=Norman_Treloar&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Norman Treloar (page does not exist)\">Norman Treloar</a>, <a href=\"/index.php?title=Brent_Knight&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Brent Knight (page does not exist)\">Brent Knight</a>, <a href=\"/Paul_Lu\" title=\"Paul Lu\">Paul Lu</a>, <a href=\"/Duane_Szafron\" title=\"Duane Szafron\">Duane Szafron</a> (<b>1992</b>). <i>A World Championship Caliber Checkers Program</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Artificial_Intelligence_%28journal%29\">Artificial Intelligence</a>, Vol. 53, Nos. 2-3, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://webdocs.cs.ualberta.ca/~duane/publications/pdf/1992ai.pdf\">pdf preprint</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Mark_Brockington\" title=\"Mark Brockington\">Mark Brockington</a>, <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Joe Culberson</a> (<b>1993</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/Camouflaging-independent-sets-in-quasi-random-Brockington-Culberson/5deeb563ef3a06bb96e31d9c480f2ab08f49f303\">Camouflaging independent sets in quasi-random graphs</a></i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://dblp.uni-trier.de/db/conf/dimacs/dimacs26.html\">Cliques, Coloring, and Satisfiability 1993</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Joe Culberson</a>, <a href=\"/Jonathan_Schaeffer\" title=\"Jonathan Schaeffer\">Jonathan Schaeffer</a> (<b>1996</b>). <i>Searching with Pattern Databases</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://dblp.uni-trier.de/db/conf/ai/ai96.html\">Canadian Conference on AI 1996</a>, </li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://github.com/basilv\">Basil Vandegriend</a>, <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Joe Culberson</a> (<b>1998</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.jair.org/index.php/jair/article/view/10213\">The Gn, m Phase Transition is Not Hard for the Hamiltonian Cycle Problem</a></i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Journal_of_Artificial_Intelligence_Research\">JAIR</a>, Vol. 9, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/1105.5443\">arXiv:1105.5443</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Joe Culberson</a> (<b>1998</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.mitpressjournals.org/doi/abs/10.1162/evco.1998.6.2.109?journalCode=evco\">On the Futility of Blind Search: An Algorithmic View of \"No Free Lunch\"</a></i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Evolutionary_Computation_(journal)\">Evolutionary Computation</a>, Vol. 6, No. 2 <sup id=\"cite_ref-10\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Joe Culberson</a>, <a href=\"/Jonathan_Schaeffer\" title=\"Jonathan Schaeffer\">Jonathan Schaeffer</a> (<b>1998</b>). <i>Pattern databases</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Computational_Intelligence_(journal)\">Computational Intelligence</a>, Vol. 14, No. 3, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://webdocs.cs.ualberta.ca/~jonathan/publications/ai_publications/Compi_.pdf\">pdf</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2000_...\">2000 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Joe_Culberson&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: 2000 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a href=\"/Mathematician#YongGao\" title=\"Mathematician\">Yong Gao</a>, <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Joe Culberson</a> (<b>2002</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://jair.org/index.php/jair/article/view/10314\">An Analysis of Phase Transition in NK Landscapes</a></i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Journal_of_Artificial_Intelligence_Research\">JAIR</a>, Vol. 17, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/1106.4575\">arXiv:1106.4575</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-11\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Mathematician#YongGao\" title=\"Mathematician\">Yong Gao</a>, <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Joe Culberson</a> (<b>2004</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://link.springer.com/chapter/10.1007/978-3-540-30201-8_5\">Consistency and Random Constraint Satisfaction Models with a High Constraint Tightness</a></i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://dblp.uni-trier.de/db/conf/cp/cp2004.html\">CP 2004</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-12\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Mathematician#YongGao\" title=\"Mathematician\">Yong Gao</a>, <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Joe Culberson</a> (<b>2007</b>). <i>Consistency and Random Constraint Satisfaction Models</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Journal_of_Artificial_Intelligence_Research\">JAIR</a>, Vol. 28, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/1110.2204\">arXiv:1110.2204</a> </li>\n<li> <a href=\"/index.php?title=Fan_Yang&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Fan Yang (page does not exist)\">Fan Yang</a>, <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Joe Culberson</a>, <a href=\"/Robert_Holte\" title=\"Robert Holte\">Robert Holte</a>, <a href=\"/Uzi_Zahavi\" title=\"Uzi Zahavi\">Uzi Zahavi</a>, <a href=\"/Ariel_Felner\" title=\"Ariel Felner\">Ariel Felner</a> (<b>2008</b>). <i>A General Theory of Additive State Space Abstractions</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Journal_of_Artificial_Intelligence_Research\">JAIR</a>, Vol. 32, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/1111.0067\">arXiv:1111.0067</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_Links\">External Links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Joe_Culberson&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: External Links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://webdocs.cs.ualberta.ca/%7Ejoe/\">Joseph (Joe) Culberson Professor</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.game-ai-forum.org/icga-tournaments/person.php?id=310\">Joe Culberson's ICGA Tournaments</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://webdocs.cs.ualberta.ca/%7Ejoe/Coloring/\">Joseph Culberson's Graph Coloring Resources Page</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://genealogy.math.ndsu.nodak.edu/id.php?id=67018\">Joseph Culberson - The Mathematics Genealogy Project</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Joe_Culberson&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap mw-references-columns\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://webdocs.cs.ualberta.ca/~chinook/authors/\">Authors - Chinook</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://webdocs.cs.ualberta.ca/~joe/Research/binary.html\">Joseph Culberson's Binary Search Tree Research</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://webdocs.cs.ualberta.ca/~joe/research.html\">Joseph Culberson Research Interests</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"/Jonathan_Schaeffer\" title=\"Jonathan Schaeffer\">Jonathan Schaeffer</a> (<b>1997, 2009</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.springer.com/gp/book/9780387765754\">One Jump Ahead</a></i>. 1. This Was Going to Be Easy, pp. 5</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://webdocs.cs.ualberta.ca/~chinook/publications/solving_checkers.html\">Chinook - Solving Checkers</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-6\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://webdocs.cs.ualberta.ca/~chinook/authors/\">Authors - Chinook</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-7\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://webdocs.cs.ualberta.ca/~joe/publications.html\">Joseph Culberson's Publications List</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-8\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_re